reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars My adult son loves it.
reviews.reviewText: My son is eighteen and loves being organized. This keeps his Bible,drawling pad,snack and anything else small so it’s all together.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Love the bag but not the strap
reviews.reviewText: I recently took this bag on a trip and love the design of it. Lots of compartments to keep things organized. I only gave it four stars because of the strap. I wish it was a little wider and more heavy duty. It’s kind of narrow and digs into your shoulder. But I’ll put up with it because I like the size and design of the bag itself.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Just what I wanted
reviews.reviewText: Great bag, good canvas, lots of storage. Got to replace a similar bag I’d had years ago and this a a near-perfect match. Wish they had different colors but it’s ok. Also a good value now, discounted by 43% so less than 20 dollars but I’d pay more.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great bag, worried about the zippers.
reviews.reviewText: So I just received this bag and so I believe its a little early for an overall review. However, I do love this bag. It was actually bigger than I had originally thought, and that's a good thing. Everything fits perfectly with room for more, love the feel of the material of the bag. My only worry is the zippers. They seem like they could break in a short time. They dont have a full smooth opening as is, hoping some breaking in will change that. But given that I've had similar bags in the past, the other bags had higher quality zippers which sometimes makes all the difference.But overall I'm liking this bag. Will update the review after some time has gone by to document how it's held up as my EDC bag.
